benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: POST Valid Payload scenarios covering multiple header variations and parameter combos (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC11, TC13, TC26).

Error handling and input validation coverage: missing/empty required header (TC06, TC07), malformed XML (TC08), empty body (TC09), invalid content type (TC10), whitespace-only payload (TC23), partial/corrupted payload (TC18), and malicious content (TC17).
Security, encoding and XML edge cases: encoding variations (TC29), CDATA/comments (TC28), Unicode and special characters (TC24).
Size and boundary coverage: very large payloads (TC12), boundary values (TC30).
Performance and resilience: load tests (TC19, TC20), network interruption (TC15), backend outage (TC16).
Regression and compatibility: duplicate versions (TC25), known-bug regression (TC21), backward compatibility with older clients (TC22).
gaps: Caching behavior for POST responses (ETag/Cache-Control) not covered (post semantics vary by API);
500 Internal Server Error scenario not tested (only 503 backend down);
Extreme header/value edge-cases and multi-value headers not explicitly tested;
recommendations: Add 500 Internal Server Error test to validate fault handling and messaging;
Add explicit 429 rate-limiting tests under high concurrency;
Add tests for caching headers on POST responses where applicable (ETag/Cache-Control);
Expand header validation tests to cover extreme or multi-value headers;
Introduce end-to-end verification after successful POST under concurrent scenarios (consistency checks).
